pumapy.io.input.import_vti(filename, voxel_length=None, import_ws=True)[source]¶

Function to import either legacy VTK file (.vtk) or vtkImageData (.vti)

Parameters

  • filename – (string) filepath and name

  • voxel_length – (float, optional) voxel_length. If None, voxel_length from the vtk file is used

  • import_ws – (bool, optional) True returns a puma.Workspace, otherwise a list of ndarrays

Returns

(Workspace or dict(string: ndarray)) If import_ws is True, then it returns a Workspace. If import_ws is False, it returns a dictionary of ndarrays as {“name1”: data1, “name2”: data2 …}

  • ws_or_nparray – (Workspace or ndarray) to be exported

pumapy.io.output.export_vti(filename, dict_data, voxel_length=None)[source]¶

Export either a puma.Workspace or numpy array to vti

Parameters

  • filename – (string) filepath and name

  • dict_data – (dict) setup as {“name1”: data1, “name2”: data2 …} containing either Workspaces or ndarrays

  • voxel_length – (float, optional) with voxel length to give to Numpy arrays (if any)

Returns

(bool) True if successful, False otherwise.

pumapy.io.output.export_weave_vtu(filename, weave, domain, max_dim_nvox, round_vox_up=True, export_orientation=True)[source]¶

Exporting weave to vtu, to be read by pumapy

Parameters

  • filename – string

  • weave – CTextile or child class of CTextile

  • domain – CDomainPlanes

  • max_dim_nvox – Number of voxels to add in the largest domain dimension

  • round_vox_up – bool, for the shorter dimensions, either round voxels up or down (+/-1 vox)

  • export_orientation – bool, specify whether to export orientation

Returns

string with filename of weave exported (input filename + dimensions)
